The paper presents a new approach to time series forecasting using machine learning models, specifically Transformer-based models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of self-attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in Natural Language Processing (NLP) tasks, indicating that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which are commonly used in the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper's focus on time series data and forecasting suggests that it may also belong to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a case study involving medical data, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
